Nova Work Tree
Purpose
The Work Tree is NovaŌĆÖs structured execution lane for multi-step work. It gives each session a persistent, governed plan so Nova can move forward deterministically instead of drifting turn-to-turn.
What it does

- Maintains a persistent task tree per session (survives restarts)
- Selects the next executable branch/task deterministically
- Enforces tool governance before any execution (required tools, allowed tools, preferred tool, explicit policy)
- Provides a concise snapshot for operator and session views

How it works

- Tree model is defined in work_tree_contracts.py
- Full runtime state (trees, branches, tasks, tooling, signals) is persisted in SQLite (runtime/work_tree.sqlite3)
- Each conversation session stores its active_work_tree_id in the session store
- On first prompt, Nova creates and binds a tree; on restart it resumes the same tree
- Planning and execution live in work_tree.py:
next_open_branch() / next_autonomous_step()
execute_autonomous_step() (real tool execution via NovaŌĆÖs existing tool path)
Completion signals and verification

- Planner hook in nova_planner_contract.py routes tree-aware prompts ("what next", "continue", "resume")

